# Implementation Plan - Fix Database Connection & Add Mock Mode

## Goal
Resolve the `psycopg2.OperationalError` caused by SSL mismatch and enable a mock database mode for testing APIs without a live database.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Utilities
#### [MODIFY] [db.py](file:///c:/Users/Yasira/Desktop/nexuscare-App/backend/src/utils/db.py)
Update [get_conn()](file:///c:/Users/Yasira/Desktop/nexuscare-App/backend/src/utils/db.py#7-16) to:
- Accept `sslmode` from environment variables (defaulting to `disable` for local dev).
- Support a `MOCK_DB` environment variable to return mock data if enabled.

### Backend Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [.env.example](file:///c:/Users/Yasira/Desktop/nexuscare-App/backend/.env.example)
Add common database environment variables:
- `DB_HOST`
- `DB_PORT`
- `DB_NAME`
- `DB_USER`
- `DB_PASSWORD`
- `SSL_MODE`
- `MOCK_DB` (true/false)

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run [app.py](file:///c:/Users/Yasira/Desktop/nexuscare-App/backend/app.py) and test `/health` endpoint.
- Use Postman to test `/api/doctor/patients/search` with both `MOCK_DB=true` and `MOCK_DB=false`.

### Manual Verification
- Verify that the `psycopg2.OperationalError` is resolved when connecting to a local database without SSL.
- Verify that Supabase connections still work with `SSL_MODE=require`.
